## Re-encoding & optimization

Why re-encode?
- Ensure broad compatibility (H.264 + AAC).
- Reduce file size or increase quality.
- Fix container/codec issues from ffmpeg.wasm.

Recommended re-encode to MP4 (H.264 + AAC):
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -c:v libx264 -preset fast -crf 18 -c:a aac -b:a 192k -movflags +faststart output_reencoded.mp4
```
- Lower CRF → higher quality (18 is visually near lossless); higher CRF (23–28) reduces size.
- `-movflags +faststart` optimizes MP4 for web streaming.

Faster / more compatible (older devices):
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -c:v libx264 -preset veryfast -crf 23 -profile:v baseline -level 3.0 -pix_fmt yuv420p -c:a aac -b:a 128k output_compatible.mp4
```

Batch re-encode multiple files (bash/powershell loop) — helpful when generating many YTPs.

