## Audio safety & ear-rape handling

YTPs often include extreme volume jumps. Before publishing, normalize and optionally limit peaks.

Normalize loudness (recommended):
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -af "loudnorm=I=-16:TP=-1.5:LRA=11" -c:v copy output_norm.mp4
```
- `I` = integrated loudness target, `TP` = true peak limit, `LRA` = loudness range.

Apply a limiter (cap peaks) — test first:
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -af "loudnorm=I=-16:TP=-1.5:LRA=11,dynaudnorm" -c:v copy output_limited.mp4
```
If you want to experiment with "ear-rape" previews locally (WARNING: very loud), you can increase volume for testing, but never upload without warning:
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -af "volume=12dB" -c:v copy output_loud.mp4
```
Always cap peaks for published versions — use loudnorm/dynaudnorm and test with headphones (start quiet).

