## Subtitles & meme text overlays

1. Soft subtitles (SRT file, selectable in players/YouTube):
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -i subs.srt -c copy -c:s mov_text output_with_subs.mp4
```
- `mov_text` is used for mp4 soft subtitles (works on many platforms including YouTube upload).

2. Burn-in subtitles or memes (drawtext) — text permanently on video (Impact meme text):
- Provide the full path to an Impact font file. Windows usually has `C:\Windows\Fonts\impact.ttf`.
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf "drawtext=fontfile='C\\:/Windows/Fonts/impact.ttf':\
text='MEME TEXT':fontcolor=white:fontsize=72:box=1:boxcolor=black@0.6:boxborderw=10:\
x=(w-text_w)/2:y=h-(text_h*1.5)" -c:a copy output_meme.mp4
```
- For dynamic text per timestamp, generate multiple drawtext filters or use an ASS subtitle file (with styling) and burn it in:
```
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf "subtitles=memes.ass" -c:a copy output_burned.mp4
```

