## Uploading to YouTube — recommended settings

Preferred format:
- Container: MP4
- Video codec: H.264 (High Profile)
- Audio codec: AAC-LC, 48 kHz, stereo
- Color: Rec.709
- Resolution & bitrates (variable):
  - 720p: 5 Mbps (approx) / CRF ~18–23
  - 1080p: 8–12 Mbps
  - 1440p / 4K: much higher — use higher bitrate or target CRF and two-pass if needed
- Frame rate: Keep original (24 / 25 / 30 / 60). Avoid re-timing unless necessary.
- Keyframe interval: 2 seconds recommended by YouTube (if controlling).

YouTube upload tip:
- Use a final file with `-movflags +faststart` for streaming.
- Include an appropriate title, description, timestamps (chapters), and content warnings (ear-rape, explicit language).
- Add captions: upload SRT to YouTube or include embedded captions as soft subtitles.

