## Windows 8.1 notes

- Use native `ffmpeg.exe` (download static build) for best compatibility/performance:
  - Add `C:\path\to\ffmpeg\bin` to PATH, or call `C:\path\to\ffmpeg\bin\ffmpeg.exe` explicitly.
- PowerShell example:
  ```
  & 'C:\ffmpeg\bin\ffmpeg.exe' -i input.mp4 -c:v libx264 -crf 23 output.mp4
  ```
- If `@ffmpeg/ffmpeg` (wasm) is used in Node on Windows 8.1, ensure `node-fetch@2` polyfill or Node >= 18 fetch support.

